Statements made as to sentencing. Additional statements made by Karla V. 

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 60 MONTHS, with credit for 88 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 24 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 36 MONTHS.  

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 36 MONTHS with the following conditions:
1) Court ordered defendant to serve 7 MONTHS condition time in the House of Correction. Defendant may participate in educational/vocational programming at the House of Correction. Defendant may have release for medical appointments, verifiable counseling appointments, and the Day Reporting Center;
2) AODA assessment and comply with any recommended treatment/counseling;
3) Pay all costs, fees, restitution and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Defendant to enter into a payment plan;
4) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge (unless previously paid);
5) Pay restitution in the amount of $2,040.00 to Eduardo C. Restitution to be paid FIRST before costs, fees and surcharges;

If revoked, court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/earnings.

If revoked, defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court ordered a restitution hearing date be set to address the restitution request for Teresa T.;

Court reinstated the cash bail in the amount of $2,500.00 previously forfeited on 2/25/15. Bail on deposit to be applied towards restitution FIRST. Any remaining amount to be applied towards costs, fees and surcharges. 

Court ordered the restitution be paid joint and several. Clerk notified by the State after the proceedings were over none of the co-actors were charged with any of the cases the defendant plead to or were read-in.


